annotationA: Oculocerebrorenal syndrome of Lowe (Ocrl) is an inositol polyphosphate 5-phosphatase that regulates PtdIns(4,5)P2 homeostasis by dephosphorylating PtdIns(4,5)P2 on endocytic compartments. In vitro experiments also suggest a role of Ocrl during cytokinesis
annotationB: Pi3K21B, isoform B; Insulin receptor substrate binding; phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase regulator activity; kinase binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: regulation of cell proliferation; regulation of cell size; insulin receptor signaling pathway; protein phosphorylation; phosphatidylinositol phosphorylation; positive regulation of growth; lipid phosphorylation; regulation of organ growth; positive regulation of cell size
